venue.name: Wood

formattedAddress: 3335 N Halsted St (at W Buckingham Pl)

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Our wood-fired oven is at the heart of it all, mustering a dynamic menu of small-plate, American fare, made with the best ingredients the season has to offer. Plus, our selection of vintage-inspired cocktails, craft beer, and wine from around the world has something for everyone to enjoy.

items.text: Really cute owner!  He looks like a cross between superman and a lumberjack
Sit at the bar. Order a cocktail and let the magic unfold.
Don't miss the charcuterie, country ham flatbread, tagliatelle, braised short ribs and the fried chicken when they're on the menu.
After 10PM go around the back and get an order of Truffle Aioli pomme frites directly from the kitchen. AMAZING and only $5.
Great staff, decadent food, and strong drinks.
Great cocktails, staff, and we loved the bacon flat bread pizza! A new favorite in Boys Town!
Order the Earls Anatomy, it's delicious and it comes in a tiny glass bathtub!
Brunch options great presentation, savory, with modest portions
Cocktails and wine list are incredible! Great service!
This place is pretty pricey, but overall the food / drinks were high quality.
Brunch was great!
overpriced for generic new american small plates
Potato gnocchi is amazing for an appetizer, we split the short ribs and scallops and both were delicious. We will definitely go back!
The venison and sweet potato sour cocktail were delicious
Great wine selection. Scribe, Scholium, and Orin Swift!
Loved the atmosphere! Good service, friendly bartenders!
Trendy, tasty, pricy
Exquisite tapas. Scallops were devine.
Vegetarian done right! Pumpkin pasta dish was amazing. Gnocchi was like none I've ever had
Fantastic vegetarian food including pappardelle and gnocchi.

venue.name: Giordano's

formattedAddress: 130 E Lake St (at N Michigan Ave)

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Welcome to Giordano's Pizza. The world's most famous stuffed pizza. Giordano's Pizza was chosen "Best Pizza in America by NBC. Chicago Tribune writes "Giordano's pizza is a must when in Chicago." New York Times posts, "The Ultimate Pizza."

pageInfo.description: Welcome to Giordano's Pizza. The world's most famous stuffed pizza. We're stuffing America one pie at a time. Giordano's Pizza was chosen "Best Pizza in America by NBC. Chicago Tribune writes "Giordano's pizza is a must when in Chicago." New York Times posts, "The Ultimate Pizza." Stop on in a Giordano's Pizza location in Chicago and now also in Florida, for a slice of heaven. Not in Chicago? Not a problem. Giordano's Pizza has made it possible to order the famous stuffed Chicago style pizza online and delivered to you any where in America.

items.text: Best pizza in America!  Make sure to order deep dish...
This is a small. Choose wisely. :)
Outstanding stuffed pizza!
Famous stuffed pizza <3 with chicken yummy
As an out-of-towner, Giordano's really lived up to its name. You cannot go wrong with any of the deep dish pizza.
If you crave Chicago's true deep dish pie and live out of town. Bring a frozen pie on the plane with you. The pies bake well and you can have a piece of Chi-town from the comfort of your couch.
For out-of-towners: No trip to Chicago is complete without a stop here. Pleasantly surprised at how good the cheese garlic bread was. Pizza is so good you may get long-distance cravings!
Great pizza! Out of towners, also try Lou Malnati's. Another good Chicago fav!
My first pie experience! I enjoyed it!
Estupendas pizzas, sólo que tardan un poco en llevarlas a tu mesa.

So I had stuffed Chicago style deep pan pizza "IN CHICAGO and it was Amazing. This is one of spots that makes it famous. Pizzas are very filling. 1 for 2/3 people will work.
extremely long wait, 45 min
Their thin crust is great! Visit their Prudential Plaza location downtown Chicago!

Went twice in two days. Exactly what Chicago pizza is supposed to be. Get it with a Goose Island.
Stuffed pizza with cheese and sausage is amazing and thats a lot considering I hate pizza. Also get the zucchini sticks!!!!
The best pizza eVer.. Get the Famous Stuffed Pizza w/ garlic & pineapple. Yumo!
the cheese bread was good and we really enjoyed the chicken sausage deep dish.  These pizzas are soooo filling

location.crossStreet: btwn S State St & S Wabash Ave
formattedAddress: 17 E Monroe St (btwn S State St & S Wabash Ave)

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: "The Chicago Hotel the World Knows Best." The hip & historic Palmer House Hilton has a history of over 140 years and after a multi-million dollar renovation continues to thrive in the heart of the theatre and financial district, just steps from the Art Institute, Millennium Park and State Street ...

pageInfo.description: Check-in for a back of house look at the world's most famous hotel brand.

items.text: Check out the beautiful ceiling in the lobby.
Check out the Peacock Door at Monroe Entrance

The hotel's haunted! Beware...
You really should stay on the Executive Level floors (22 & 23). Super-nice!
The hotel’s gilded two-story lobby features overhead murals depicting scenes from Greek mythology.

venue.name: Gramercy Tavern

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: A revival and renewal of the classic American tavern, Gramercy Tavern offers refined, seasonal cuisine from Chef Michael Anthony.

items.text: CNN Eatocracy: It's one of the New York's most beloved restaurants -- and for good reason with its luxurious yet homey atmosphere. Everything's seasonal and you really can't go wrong.
The unofficial official First Restaurant of New York. Though its formal dining room is a bit too too for Eater 38 contention, the front room and its seasonal American menu wins. [Eater 38 Member]
Jimmy Fallon: "This is my favorite restaurant in New York. Everything is good here." He's a particular fan of the venison tartare.
Gramercy Tavern is one of the NYT restaurant critic Sam Sifton’s 50 favorite NYC restaurants. To see the full list, get The Scoop iPhone app, an inside guide to New York: NYTimes.com/thescoop
In the tavern section, great food and drinks can be had at a fraction of the cost of a meal in the main dining room.
Gansevoort Recommend
Great food and wine list. It is always consistent and has the best atmosphere. I love to eat at the bar where it is more casual and fun. -Carmen Gonzalez, Top Chef
Ladies room mirror is a skinny mirror.
The cheeseburger is the best off-menu item in NYC, making our list of "The Tastes That Make the City: NYC Edition."

user.firstName: The Tastes that Make the City

items.text: Do what you love in life and happiness follows.  Like lunch a Gramercy Tavern with my gnome Klaus.

The restaurant’s no-reservations front room is that rare space that’s sexy enough for a date but comfortable enough for your grandparents, and the menu is so thoughtful it’s like an act of generosity.
The best black cod I've ever had. Chef Michael Anthony is a true artist. -Ron Duprat, Top Chef
Bill Addison's review: "I loved the way Michael Anthony used pork in ways usually associated for beef. A piggy Bolognese tossed with tagliatelle had an appealing unctuousness and meaty bite."
There's nothing better on a summer's evening than a seasonal peach dessert. Head to Gramercy Tavern to try the peach-and-blueberry shortcake, with pecan and lemon- verbena ice-cream. Delicious!
Perfectly seasonal standouts have included butternut squash soup, duck breast over parsnip purée, and tarte tatin. – Green Guide Editor
Get the roasted oysters if they're on the menu.  You're welcome.

Next time you want to eat here an font have a reservation, just sit at the bar and get the $16 soup-and-sandwich set. For just a little more than you'd normally pay for a crappy lunch, you get A+ food
Great burger for lunch, not on the menu...pssst
One Michelin star.
Best seasonal dishes!  And also known as the first restaurant in New York!
